{"article_id":"XvZ3NeUGSXsjGPpP","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Teachers in Chicago walked off the job Monday","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"after contract negotiations fell through ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"leaving 400,000 students in the nation 's third-largest district shut out of their classrooms .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"Contract talks broke down late last night ,","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"and by Monday morning Chicago public school teachers , many","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"wearing red T-shirts","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"and carrying signs ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"were picketing around the city for the first time in a quarter-century .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"At a news conference late Sunday , Chicago Mayor Rahm Emanuel called the teachers ' move a `` strike of choice . ''","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"Emanuel says","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"the union walked away from the table too soon .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"`` We 're down to two issues .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Finish it !","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"Let the kids go back","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"where they belong , ''","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"he said late Sunday .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"`` This is not the right thing","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"to do to the children .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"It 's unnecessary .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"It 's avoidable","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"and it 's wrong . ''","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"But Chicago Teachers Union President Karen Lewis said","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"there has n't been enough movement on job protection , class sizes and teacher evaluations .","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"`` We demand a fair contract now ,","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"and","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"until there 's one in place","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"that our members will accept ,","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"we will be on the line , ''","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"she said .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"Board President David Vitale said","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"after the teachers rejected a 16 percent pay raise over four years and a number of other benefits ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"there was little more","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"that could be offered .","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"`` There is only so much money in the system , ''","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Vitale said .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"`` This is not a small commitment","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"we 're handing out at a time","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"when our fiscal situation is really challenged . ''","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"Becky Vevea , of member station WBEZ , reports","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"that school leaders and Emanuel : `` ... want big changes similar to ones","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"being pushed nationally","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"- a longer school day , longer school year , a new system","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"for grading teachers","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"and a whole new way","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"to pay them . ``","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"The teachers union is pushing back on those efforts ,","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"arguing for Emanuel to invest in what they say","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"are under-resourced neighborhood schools . ''","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"Vevea reports","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"that it 's an awkward time for the union","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"because unemployment is high","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"and district budgets are being cut .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"It could also be awkward for the Obama administration .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Education Secretary Arne Duncan ran the Chicago schools for years ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"and Emanuel is a former administration chief of staff .","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"Rhoda Gutierrez , a parent with two kids in public school , told WBEZ","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"that the politicians in Washington , D.C. , need to step in .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"`` This is where Obama came from ;","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"this is where Duncan came from , ''","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"Gutierrez said .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"`` The policies in Chicago have gone national and viral . ''","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"According to The Chicago Tribune ,","depth":3},{"id":62,"text":"144 of the district 's schools will be staffed with nonunion employees ,","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"including principals and assistant principals ,","depth":5},{"id":64,"text":"to provide services and meals .","depth":4},{"id":65,"text":"The New York Times quotes the CTU 's Lewis as saying","depth":4},{"id":66,"text":"the contingency plan for students is `` a mess ''","depth":5},{"id":67,"text":"and that school officials were expecting families to `` put their children with random folks . ''","depth":5},{"id":68,"text":"High School teacher Steve Parsons said","depth":5},{"id":69,"text":"he and others are `` ready to stay out","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"as long as it takes to get a fair contract","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"and protect our schools , ''","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"according to The Times .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":145,"left":133,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":80,"right":132,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":80,"left":75,"right":79,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":75,"left":74,"right":2,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":74,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":79,"left":3,"right":78,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":78,"left":77,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":77,"left":4,"right":76,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":76,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":132,"left":109,"right":131,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":109,"left":92,"right":108,"relation":"adversative","nucleari